description: information about plants that are food

command.prompt:
Generate 3 rows for a table of information about plants that are food. The semi-colon-separated header of attributes for the table is:
Plant;Variety;Color;Fruit;Soil;Water;Temperature;Light;Pruning;Fertilizer;Pest;Taste;Days to Maturity;Nutrition Facts (per 100g)

Do not generate fictional rows. Generate the rows from real known data. Here is a list of semi-colon-separated rows not to generate by semantic key only:
Plant;Variety
Apple;Granny Smith
Asparagus;Jersey Knight
Basil, Sweet;Summer
Broccoli;Spring
Cabbage;Fall
Cherry;Rainier
Cucumber;Lemon
Eggplant;Neon
Grape;Concord
Lettuce;Romaine
Peach;August Pride
Pear;Bartlett
Radish;Cherry Belle
Raspberry;Bountiful
Spinach;Space
Squash;Acorn
Strawberry;Temptation
Tomato;Beefsteak
Watermelon;Crimson Sweet

Output the rows in the format of a semi-colon-separated .csv file with a column header. Then explain the source of the new data.
command.output_table:
Plant;Variety;Color;Fruit;Soil;Water;Temperature;Light;Pruning;Fertilizer;Pest;Taste;Days to Maturity;Nutrition Facts (per 100g)
Carrot, Daucus carota;Danvers 126;Orange;Root;Loamy, well-drained;Medium;15-20°C;Full sun;Light;Complete organic fertilizer;Carrot fly, Aphids;Sweet, crunchy;70-80 days;Vitamin A, Dietary fiber, Potassium, Biotin
Celery, Apium graveolens;Ventura;Green;Stalk;Loamy, moist;High;10-20°C;Full sun;Moderate;Complete organic fertilizer;Aphids, Whiteflies;Crisp, slightly bitter;120-150 days;Vitamin K, Vitamin C, Potassium, Folate
Corn, Zea mays;Sweet Corn Incredible;Yellow;Ear;Fertile, well-drained;High;21-27°C;Full sun;Heavy;Complete organic fertilizer;Corn earworm, Northern corn leaf blight;Sweet, starchy;75-100 days;Carbohydrates, Dietary fiber, Protein, Vitamin B6
command.epilogue: The data for these rows is sourced from various agricultural extension websites, such as the University of Illinois Extension, North Carolina State University Extension, and the University of California Master Gardener Program. These sources provide detailed growing guidelines and recommendations for various plant varieties, which I have condensed into the attributes presented in the table.

Pest.2: Corn earworm, Northern corn leaf blight

Nutrition Facts (per 100g).0: Vitamin A, Dietary fiber, Potassium, Biotin
Nutrition Facts (per 100g).1: Vitamin K, Vitamin C, Potassium, Folate
Nutrition Facts (per 100g).2: Carbohydrates, Dietary fiber, Protein, Vitamin B6
